{"lemma":"رِضَى","slug":"رِضَى","root":"ر.ض.#","root_slug":"ر-ض-_","root_link":"/words/roots/ر-ض-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"رِضَى","root":"رضو","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["name","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n15771","n15776","n15777","n15782"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B1%D9%90%D8%B6%D9%8E%D9%89"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"name","gloss":"Ruḍaw, a pre-Islamic Arabian god later misinterpreted as the name of a place of worship."},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"alternative form of رِضًا (riḍan)","tags":["alt-of","alternative"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the root ر ض و (r ḍ w), meaning \"the contented one\". Attested as both Safaitic 𐪇𐪓𐪅 (rḍw) and 𐪇𐪓𐪚 (rḍy), and Dumaitic 𐪇𐪓𐪅 (rḍw)."},"ipa":["/ru.dˤaː/","/ri.dˤan/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n15771","headword_ar":"رَضِىَ","root":"rDw","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"is originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raDiwa","text_ar":"رَضِوَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"being changed into"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"because of the kesreh: (S:) the tribe of Teiyi said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raDaA","text_ar":"رَضَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raDiYa","text_ar":"رَضِىَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (IDrd in his lex., cited by Freytag; and Mughnee voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilaY","text_ar":"اـِلَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"there said to be a dial. var. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raDiYa","text_ar":"رَضِىَ"},{"kind":"text","text":".) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raDiYa Eanohu","text_ar":"رَضِىَ عَنْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Msb, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealayohi","text_ar":"عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, Msb, K,) which is of the dial. of the people of El-Hijáz, (Msb,) the verb being thus made trans. by means of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ElY","text_ar":"على"},{"kind":"text","text":", accord. to Ks, agreeably with the opinion of Sb respecting instances of this kind, for the purpose of making it to accord with its contr.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saxiTa","text_ar":"سَخِطَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, TA,) aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaroDaY","text_ar":"يَرْضَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riDFY","text_ar":"رِضًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruDFY","text_ar":"رُضًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riDowaAnN","text_ar":"رِضْوَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruDowaAnN","text_ar":"رُضْوَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, * M, Msb, * K,) the last of the dial. of Keys and Temeem, (Msb, TA,) and mentioned by Sb, (M, TA,) but all the readers of the Kur read"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rDwAn","text_ar":"رضوان"},{"kind":"text","text":"with kesr, except 'Ásim, who is related to have read it with damm, (T, TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maroDaApN","text_ar":"مَرْضَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, * M, K,) originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maroDawapN","text_ar":"مَرْضَوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was pleased, well pleased, content, contented,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"satisfied, with him; regarded him with good will,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"favour;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"liked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"approved, him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(MA;) [i. e., as said above,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saxiTa","text_ar":"سَخِطَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, Msb, K;) the object being a person: (Msb:) and Sb states that they also said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raDoyuwA","text_ar":"رَضْيُوا"},{"kind":"text","text":", with the medial radical quiescent, for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raDuwA","text_ar":"رَضُوا"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but it is extr. (M, TA.) The saying in the Kur [v. last verse but one, and ix. 101, &c.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raDiYa A@ll~`hu Eanohumo waraDuwA Eanohu","text_ar":"رَضِىَ ا@للّٰهُ عَنْهُمْ وَرَضُوا عَنْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God is well pleased with them and they are well pleased with Him"},{"kind":"text","text":"] means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God is well pleased with their deeds and they are well pleased with the recompense that He has bestowed upon them:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA:) or, accord. to Er-Rághib,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riDaY AlEabodi","text_ar":"رِضَى العَبْدِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eani A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"عَنِ ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The servant's,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"man's, being not displeased with that which God's decree has made to happen to him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riDaY A@ll~`hi Eini AlEabodi","text_ar":"رِضَى ا@للّٰهِ عِنِ العَبْدِ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God's seeing the servant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"man, to be obedient to that which He has commanded, and refraining from that which He has forbidden."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raDiytuhu","text_ar":"رَضِيتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raDiytu bihi","text_ar":"رَضِيتُ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riDFY","text_ar":"رِضًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA) [and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruDFY","text_ar":"رُضًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riDowaAnN","text_ar":"رِضْوَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c., as above]; and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AirotaDayotuhu","text_ar":"اِرْتَضَيْتُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I was pleased, well pleased, content, contented,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"satisfied, with it; regarded it with good will,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"favour;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"liked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"approved, it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(MA: [for the verb is there said to have the same signification in the phrases"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raDiyahu","text_ar":"رَضِيَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raDiYa bihi","text_ar":"رَضِىَ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as it has in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raDiYa","text_ar":"رَضِىَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eanohu","text_ar":"عَنْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealayohi","text_ar":"عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ArtDAh","text_ar":"ارتضاه"},{"kind":"text","text":"is there similarly explained: and the like is implied in the S and K; and is evidently agreeable with general usage:]) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he chose it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"preferred it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA:) the object being a thing: (S, Msb, TA:) or (accord. to explanations of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taroDaAhaA","text_ar":"تَرْضَاهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the Kur ii. 139)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I loved it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"liked it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ksh, Bd, Jel;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inclined to it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ksh;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"had a desire for it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd.) The saying of the lawyers, [respecting a woman whose consent to her marriage has been asked,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ya$ohadu EalaY riDaAhaA","text_ar":"يَشْهَدُ عَلَى رِضَاهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. her silence]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"testifies,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"declares, her permission"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"consent"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; because permission indicates"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riDFY","text_ar":"رِضًى"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raDiytu bihi SaAHibFA","text_ar":"رَضِيتُ بِهِ صَاحِبًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I was pleased with him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I liked him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"approved him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chose him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"preferred him, as a companion"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raDiyahu li*`lika AlA^amori","text_ar":"رَضِيَهُ لِذٰلِكَ الاَمْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ArtDAhu","text_ar":"ارتضاهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", [which may be well rendered"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He approved him for that thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he saw him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"judged him, to be fit for that thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affair."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liSuHobatihi waxidomatihi","text_ar":"لِصُحْبَتِهِ وَخِدْمَتِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ArtDAhu","text_ar":"ارتضاهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"approved him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chose him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"preferred him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"saw him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"judged him, to be fit; for his companionship, and his service."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruDiyato maEy$atuhu","text_ar":"رُضِيَتْ مَعيشَتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His living,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sustenance, was found pleasing, well pleasing, contenting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"satisfying;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was liked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"approved"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: one should not say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raDiyatp","text_ar":"رَضِيَتة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in this case]. (S, K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raDawotuhu","text_ar":"رَضَوْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,) aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroDuwhu","text_ar":"اَرْضُوهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I surpassed him in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riDFY","text_ar":"رِضًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. in"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being pleased, well pleased, content,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: see above, second sentence]: (S, * M, K *:) so in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraDawotuhu","text_ar":"فَرَضَوْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raADaAniY","text_ar":"رَاضَانِى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He vied,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contended, with me in being pleased, well pleased, content,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and I surpassed him therein"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, M, K:) the inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rADAnY","text_ar":"راضانى"},{"kind":"text","text":"thus used is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muraADaApN","text_ar":"مُرَاضَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riDaA='N","text_ar":"رِضَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M;) both these signify the same (K, TA) as inf. ns. of this verb. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","Msb","K","TA","T"]},{"entry_id":"n15776","headword_ar":"رُضًى","root":"rDw","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain idol-temple, belonging to"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the tribe of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Rabee'ah:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) whence they gave the name of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eabodu ruDFY","text_ar":"عَبْدُ رُضًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Servant of Rudà"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K"]},{"entry_id":"n15777","headword_ar":"رِضًى","root":"rDw","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"is merely an inf. n., (S,) [as such]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maroDaApN","text_ar":"مَرْضَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) meaning The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being pleased, well pleased, content,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.; [see 1;]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saxaTN","text_ar":"سَخَطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M:) and the simple subst. is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riDaA='N","text_ar":"رِضَا=ءٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", with medd.; [signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a state of being pleased,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.;] (Akh, S;) or the latter is only an inf. n. of 3, (M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muraADaApN","text_ar":"مُرَاضَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, K:) [but] the former [is also used as a subst., signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"content,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"approval:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"permission,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"consent:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and] is dualized, app. as meaning the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kind"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mode"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner, of being pleased,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]: (M:) the dual is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riDawaAnK","text_ar":"رِضَوَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riDayaAni","text_ar":"رِضَيَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, M, K:) Ks heard"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riDawaAni","text_ar":"رِضَوَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamawaAni","text_ar":"حَمَوَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as duals of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riDFY","text_ar":"رِضًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HimFY","text_ar":"حِمًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and says that the proper way is to say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riDayaAni","text_ar":"رِضَيَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HimayaAni","text_ar":"حِمَيَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [which in the case of the former is strange, as its final radical is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":",] but that the pronunciation with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the more common: (S:) and accord. to some,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maraADK","text_ar":"مَرَاضٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an irreg. pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riDFY","text_ar":"رِضًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but others say that it is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maroDaApN","text_ar":"مَرْضَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA faEalotuhu Eino riDaAhu","text_ar":"مَا فَعَلْتُهُ عِنْ رِضَاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riDowatihi","text_ar":"رِضْوَتِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see the latter, below. (Z, K.) ―         -b2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raADK","text_ar":"رَاضٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", latter sentence.       -A2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN riDFY","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ رِضًى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qawomN riDFY","text_ar":"قَوْمٌ رِضًى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a people,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"party,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with whom one is pleased, well pleased, contented,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"satisfied; regarded with good will,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"favour; liked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"approved;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maroDiY~N","text_ar":"مَرْضِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qunoEaAnN","text_ar":"قُنْعَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riDFY","text_ar":"رِضًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"being, thus used, an inf. n. in the sense of a pass. part. n., like as the inf. n. is used in the sense of an act. part. n. in the instance of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EadolN","text_ar":"عَدْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaSomN","text_ar":"خَصْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M.) ―         -b2-  [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raDiY~N","text_ar":"رَضِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; for which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riDFY","text_ar":"رِضًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riDFA","text_ar":"رِضًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"seems to be erroneously substituted, in two senses, in some copies of the K.]"}],"source_refs":["S","K","M"]},{"entry_id":"n15782","headword_ar":"رَضِىٌّ","root":"rDw","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raADK","text_ar":"رَاضٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-  Also, (K, TA,) i. e. like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ganiY~N","text_ar":"غَنِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) [in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~iDaY","text_ar":"الرِّضَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", and in my MS. copy of the K"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~iDaA","text_ar":"الرِّضَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", are put in the place of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~aDiY~u","text_ar":"الرَّضِىُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] One"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who is responsible, accountable,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"answerable;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaAminN","text_ar":"ضَامِنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": so in the copies of the K, and in like manner in the Tekmileh: accord. to the copies of the T,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaAmirN","text_ar":"ضَامِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lean,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"light of flesh,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (TA.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Loving; a lover;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a friend."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, K, TA.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Obeying,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"obedient."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA"]}]}}